events.name: (CS)²AI Online™ Replay: Developing OT IR Proactive and Reactive Programs
events.description:
https://attendee.gotowebinar.com/register/1597777752948496216?source=08072024meetupevent

Join us and industrial cyber security exec leader Bryan Singer as he shares his experiences handling OT cyber incidents and how proactive and reactive incident response activities between IT and OT are creating dynamic and adaptable cyber risk mitigation strategies. In this session he covers the particular challenges of OT cyber incident response and give us some hard lessons learned from the field in helping companies handle their worst days ever.

Bryan is a Principal Director of Security Innovation for Accenture, where he operates as Jedi Master of all things ICS and IoT, leading Red Teaming, penetration testing,critical vulnerability analysis, and more. His background is all with top-shelf control system cyber security firms, including technical and leadership roles at Red Trident, IOActive, Kenexis, Wurldtech, Rockwell Automation and Raytheon. He has an extensive background in several industries, including manufacturing, DoD, and healthcare. His proven professional skills include system architecture and design, software project management, application development, system administration, network administration, database design and administration, and multi-tier support.

events.name: (CS)²AI Online™: Keeping Us Alive- Medical Device & Healthcare System Cybersec
events.description:
Register now! https://attendee.gotowebinar.com/register/2395207357219462237?source=08142024meetupevent

Whether it's the pacemaker in your chest or the gas distribution control system in your hospital, medical devices and healthcare systems are the most clearly designed and used to protect human lives. Tens of millions of us depend on their uninterrupted operations every day. Join us to learn what is happening in this field.
\- Are medical devices and healthcare \(and building control\) systems being designed with cybersecurity in mind?
\- Are they designed for safe and secure updating and upgrading?
\- How much of what's out there is still legacy\, with no cybersecurity at all?
\- What regulations are relevant here?
\- Where are we seeing improvements \(and where aren't we seeing them\)?
Panelists:
Marie Moe, Senior Consultant at Google (Mandiant), Associate Professor at Norwegian University of Science and Technology, and Honorary Senior Research Fellow at Imperial College London

Billy Rios, Co Founder of QED Solutions, Author, Security Researcher, Venture Adviser, Entrepreneur and CS2AI Fellow

name: Tech MKE - Milwaukee's Full Stack Meetup Group

events.name: Saturday Workgroup (Virtual)
events.description:
Let's hang out and work on our games online! Bring a coffee and your latest project if you'd like to share.

We're meeting on Discord for it's better video sharing capabilities. If you don't already have an account, no worries!, you'll be prompted to provide one upon joining the channel.

Here's our typical agenda:
1. Idle Chatter
2. Area Events and Happenings
3. Scheduling Presentations (making sure all attendees who want to present have time)
4. Presentations

We like to take screenshots of the presentations to post here on Meetup.com, so others get a sense of what we do and the cool projects that come through here. Screenshots are attributed with the name of the work (as best known) and the presenter's name or online handle, as per their preference. We're guessing that if you're wanting to show off your projects in the meetup, it isn't a stretch to have a screenshot posted here on the site as well. BUT! If you'd rather not have your work posted on Meetup.com, or you have another concern, please let a host know and we'll accommodate you as best we can.

events.name: Maximizing Collaboration and Productivity with Atlassian Solutions
events.description:
*Join us for an exclusive in-person event on August 15th in Chicago as we delve into the transformative power of collaboration on the Atlassian Cloud Platform.*

As the organizational and technological landscape evolves, enhancing collaboration becomes crucial. This event will empower you to unlock the potential of these powerful tools, foster team collaboration, and embrace innovative practices. Our interactive session will help you maximize your use of Atlassian solutions and harness AI capabilities to elevate your projects.

### Key Highlights:

* Collaborative Practices: Learn how to effectively gather project plans, product requirements, meeting notes, and collaborate on ideas.
* Knowledge Base Establishment: Understand the best practices for setting up a comprehensive knowledge base for your teams.
* Demo: Live overview of the collaboration capabilities across Jira, Confluence, Jira Service Management (JSM), and Loom. We will highlight some AI capabilities that enhance collaboration and overall productivity.

### Overview of the solutions:

* **Jira**: Dream it, plan it, launch it. The #1 tool for agile teams is now for all teams. Plan, track, and deliver your biggest ideas together.
* **Confluence**: Scale your knowledge. Connect and consolidate scattered docs and disconnected teammates in one central source of truth.
* **Jira Service Management**: Deliver service faster. Connect Dev and Ops teams on a single platform with customizable features and AI-powered agents.
* **Loom**: Record, share, collaborate. Record and share AI-powered video messages to reach a broader audience for better async collaboration.

This session will include best practices and real-life examples of how our customers leverage AI potential with Atlassian solutions. Your questions and insights are highly encouraged, making this an interactive and engaging experience.

Following the presentation, join us for a reception and networking event where you can continue discussing with our experts over complimentary food and drinks. There is no charge for this event, but spaces are limited, so secure your spot soon.

We look forward to seeing you there as we dive into the world of enhanced collaboration and innovative solutions with Herzum.

events.name: Accelerate your ITAM with Atlassian Assets and Flexera One
events.description:
Managing your assets has never been more critical in today's remote work environment. Adopting Atlassian solutions can simplify, streamline, and automate your business processes, helping to increase productivity and reduce technology costs. Combining Atlassian Assets with Flexera One solution will propel your asset tracking to new heights.

**What types of assets do you need to manage?** You can track physical assets (like laptops or an entire office), virtual assets (such as software licenses or payment platforms), and even personnel (like employees). Join Herzum's highly regarded Atlassian Tools webinar series this month to learn how to use Jira Service Management for Asset and Configuration Management integrated with Flexera One.

In this live, interactive webinar, we will cover:

* What types of assets does your company need to track and why?
* The benefits of modern asset tracking for your organization.
* Automating your employee onboarding and offboarding processes.
* Monitor assets from initial purchase through disposal.
* Best practices for implementing an asset management system.

This webinar is perfect for organizations new to Atlassian and those already leveraging its capabilities.

**Register now!**

events.description:
August 14th will be the August Code + Brews! This event will be sponsored and hosted by [Northern Ground](https://www.northernground.com/). Join us for some coding, beer, and pizza!

We are excited to invite you to our upcoming networking and coding event. This gathering is designed to foster connections within our local tech community. Whether you are a seasoned professional, a hobbyist, or just getting your feet wet in the world of coding, there's a place for you here. The event will offer opportunities for both individual coding and collaborative projects, accommodating different styles and preferences. If you'd prefer to engage in insightful conversations and discussions, you will find plenty of fellow software developers eager to share their experiences and ideas. Our goal is to facilitate a relaxed environment where knowledge exchange, collaboration, and innovation are the natural outcomes.

We look forward to seeing you there, and can't wait to see the magic that happens when our diverse community comes together.

events.name: Getting Started with Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)
events.description:
Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) seems to be the most popular way people are using AI in their own applications. If you have any business applications that could be enhanced by adding the ability to search your data (database or documents) using a ChatGPT like interaction, then RAG may be the starting point for you.
In this session, I will do a quick introduction of the parts of a RAG implementation - though I do assume you are already familiar with what Large Language Models (LLM's) are and how to use them. The majority of the session will be spent looking at different ways to implement the RAG pattern using .NET with Azure and OpenAI services. We'll start with a simple naïve implementation and get into more detail on ways to improve the functionality.
Demos include:

1. A simple local Blazor web application using SQL Server and Azure Open AI to understand RAG, vectors/embeddings
2. A full featured RAG application with a Blazor front-end and Azure AI Search for storing vectors for searching unstructured data (ie. Pdf files)
3. An additional demo that shows RAG with structured data (semantic search on data from a database) also written in .NET

Watch live on YouTube if you are not able to be there: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JMX-qyRuAzE](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JMX-qyRuAzE)

Location Sponsor: **[Concurrency](https://concurrency.com/)**
Food Sponsor: **[TEKSystems](https://www.teksystems.com/)**
